Jessica Silva visited the home of James Polkinghorne's father to explain why she had to kill his son .
The 60-year-old spoke for the first time about the day, Mother's Day 2012, when she stabbed and killed her partner .
She said she was living in fear and violence and told no one else to make the same mistakes .
Michael Usher, the father of her son's young son, said the ordeal had so destroyed Jessica's life .
He said: 'It's only the start of a process, there is no neat ending at all'